# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECRETS — never commit these. (SRS-NFR-04)
# A leaked OpenAI key can be used by strangers and billed to us.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.key
*.pem
secrets.json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PERSONAL / LEAD-ONLY — never publish to the team repo.
# Private management + coaching notes. Ignoring them here means
# they stay on your computer but never reach GitHub, even with
# `git add -A`. To share one later, delete its line below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All my personal files now live in this one folder — ignoring it keeps them all out:
_lead-private/

# (kept as a safety net, in case a personal file is ever created outside that folder)
LEAD_BRIEF.md
AAAI_Tracker.md
AAAI - Project Tracking Weekly.pdf
AAAI_Week*_Restart_Tasks.md
AAAI_Prompt-Log.md
AAAI_Document_Brief_*.docx
Claude Prompt.pdf
AAAI_OPPM*
Internship Schedule.txt

# Local scratch folder (screenshots, personal notes) — not team work
Github_Repo/

# ── Python / FastAPI (backend) ──
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# ── Node / React / Vite (frontend) ──
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.vite/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# ── Candidate audio & uploads ──
# Git is bad at large binary files. Audio lives on disk/object storage;
# the database stores only the path (see `responses.audio_path`).
media/
uploads/
*.webm
*.mp4
*.wav
*.m4a
*.mp3

# ── Database ──
*.sqlite3
*.db
*.dump

# ── OS / editor noise ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# ── Logs ──
*.log
logs/

# ── Local-only helper files (not for the team repo) ──
# Github_Repo/ holds personal screenshots; the PUSH-* file is a how-to guide.
Github_Repo/
PUSH-AAAI-to-GitHub_step-by-step.md
